The paper focuses on improving single image super resolution using example-based methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The techniques presented also involve the use of machine learning and optimization, which are common in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of image processing techniques such as back projection refinement and context reasoning, which are relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
